// ============================================================
//  RoboNav v7 — ESP32 + Phone Gyro Turns + Obstacle Detection
//
//  NEW IN v7:
//   * GYRO HEADING-HOLD on forward AND backward: holds a straight
//     line using the phone yaw (compensates weight/wheel veer on
//     rough floors). Falls back to encoder sync if phone drops.
//   * RUNTIME obstacle distance: "ODIST:<cm>" sets danger threshold
//     live (no reflash). Default raised 25 -> 50 cm.
//   * Obstacle detection ON/OFF: "ODET:1" / "ODET:0".
//   * Turn & nudge speeds settable live: "SPDT:<pwm>" / "SPDN:<pwm>".
//   * Active brake pulse on obstacle stop (snappier, less coast).
//   * MQTT is pumped during forward/backward so yaw stays fresh.
//
//  CHANGES vs v5 (per field testing):
//   * RELIABLE ULTRASONIC: one ping per cycle (HC-SR04 needs ~60ms
//     between pings — v5 fired 3 pings 0.8ms apart which produced
//     garbage). Detection now uses HYSTERESIS (closeHits 0..3, trips
//     at >=2) so a single dropped read no longer flips the result.
//   * SERVO IS NOT MOVED. It is centered once in setup() and held
//     straight. No sweep. (We'll add scanning back later.)
//   * LIVE DISTANCE: every ping is published to robot/obstacle (with
//     DET:0 until a real trip) so the web app can show distance live
//     and draw the radar dot correctly.
//   * TIERED NUDGE CORRECTION for turns:
//        |err|>20  -> big nudge   (fast)
//        |err|>10  -> medium
//        |err|>5   -> small
//        |err|<=5  -> precise (the original 40ms that works great)
//   * TURN ABORT RELAXED: removed the ">20deg => stop" rule that
//     randomly killed good turns. Now only stops on GENUINE
//     divergence (error grows for several nudges in a row).
//
//  MQTT
//    SUB : robot/control  (EXEC / DRIVE / SPD / S / SCAN)
//          robot/gyro
//    PUB : robot/status   ("done" / "obstacle")
//          robot/gyro_cmd ("RESET")
//          robot/obstacle ("DET:0|DIST:42.0|ANG:0|REMAIN:0|CMD:F|MODE:drive")
// ============================================================

